Between 20 and 50 Dead in Blaze at Theatre in Gutenberg in Southern Sweden

Stockholm 10-30 (AFP) - Swedish police announced that at least 20 people, mostly young people, died in a blaze that broke out the night of Thursday-Friday in a theatre in Gutenberg in (south).

Police spokesman, Lars Hasson, explained that the total is not exactly known yet, but it "may be much higher".  He had earlier spoken about the loss of fifty dead.

He added that the reasons behind the blaze are not known yet, explaining that the fire broke out at about 01:00 at dawn today, Friday (00:00 GMT) in a disco behind the theatre.

More than one hundred firemen and tens of ambulances are on the scene.
